ical landscape, often characterized as the most prominent conservative voice in mostly liberal Hollywood. At Eastwood’s late age, his critical success as actor and director, his combative willingness to confront serious cultural issues in his films, and his undeniable talent behind the camera all call for a new and comprehensive study that considers and contextualizes his multiple roles, both on and off screen. Tough Ain’t Enough offers readers a series of original essays by prominent cinema scholars that explore the actor-director’s extensive career. The result is a far-reaching and nuanced portrait of one of America’s most prolific and thoughtful filmmakers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aClint Eastwood.  aEastwood.  aHollywood.  aactor.  adirector.  afilm.  afilmmaker.1 aBolton, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBolton, Lucy.1 aCarson, Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarson, Diane.1 aDesser, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDesser, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDesser, David.1 aFriedman, Lester D.1 aFriedman, Lester D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedman, Lester D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKeller, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeller, Alexandra.1 aKirshner, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirshner, Jonathan.1 aLofthouse, Charity, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLofthouse, Charity.1 aPomerance, Murray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 a